The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 16 May is 42,143 (4,877.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 11 May, there were 120 new confirmed cases (13.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 04 May, there were 107 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 12% (13 extra cases).
